</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> No, the factions work, but they may take a while. An ogre was

<BR>&gt; able to walk and perform transactions in any town that opposed
<BR>&gt; ogres. It took him a long time of concentrated effort to do so
<BR>&gt; however. He was 10th level minimum (not on a PvP server) when he
<BR>&gt; was able to do it AND he focused on changing his faction.
<BR>&gt; Another big consideration is what diety you initially choose.
<BR>&gt; Necro's are restricted to evil gods, which usually doesn't bode
<BR>&gt; well with many good NPCs.
<P>Nice, yea but that is agonistic ogre I think. How does it work with evil gods? I don't want to oppose my gods, all I want is that merchants like me :) Perhaps they hate dwarf paladins ? :)
<P>&gt; I believe factions are designed to be something you just can
<BR>&gt; turn on and off from a few hours of work.
<P>Yea I know this too, and its good and should be like this, but perhaps one should be informed that *progress* is happening, I mean you know spending a month killing kobolds just to gain gnome attention and then I find out that the feature was turned off, you know sorta wasted time...doesn't bode well for Verant..
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
